<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="32" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d32">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 863.0011/10.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Emperor</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Deeply sensible of the condolence you have kindly transmitted to me in
                            the name of the Government and people of the United States, I beg you to
                            accept therefor and for the expression of your own sympathy my sincerest
                            and cordial thanks.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Franz Joseph</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>